The paper proposes practical components to speed up deep reinforcement learning algorithms for tactical decision making in autonomous driving systems. This involves the use of artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the cs.AI sub-category. The focus on decision making for autonomous driving also suggests relevance to the cs.RO sub-category, which deals with robotics and control systems. The use of deep learning algorithms and evaluation in a driving simulator suggests relevance to the cs.LG and cs.CV sub-categories, which deal with machine learning and computer vision. Finally, the application of these techniques to autonomous driving systems suggests relevance to the cs.SY sub-category, which deals with systems and control.
